  "market_context": "NQ on 11/8/2023 reached a daily-chart sellside liquidity level (daily swing low). The analyst dropped from the daily to the 5-minute chart to observe how price would react at this higher-time-frame level during the early session.",
  "key_observation": "After tagging the daily swing low, a full-bodied down-close candle swept the lows on the 5-minute, then price displaced and closed above that single down-close candle, which then acted as a bullish order block supporting price higher into a fair value gap.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the daily-chart sellside liquidity (swing low) as the important higher-time-frame level.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 5-minute chart and observe price hitting that daily swing low.",
    "Step 3: Wait for displacement back up; note the first attempt lacks a clean full-bodied candle into the low.",
    "Step 4: Observe a full-bodied down-close candle that sweeps the lows, creating a lower-time-frame liquidity sweep.",
    "Step 5: Confirm displacement and closure above the high of that down-close candle.",
    "Step 6: Mark the opening price of the sweeping down-close candle as the bullish order block and look for it to support price higher.",
    "Step 7: Note the fair value gap below and allow price to reach into it; wicks tap the FVG while bodies respect the order block.",
    "Step 8: Confirm price uses the down-close candle as support and continues higher."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price respected the order block (bodies held above it while wicks filled the FVG) and continued higher as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "When price taps a higher-time-frame level, look for a lower-time-frame full-bodied opposing candle that sweeps liquidity; once price displaces and closes through it, that candle becomes a valid order block supporting the new direction, even if price first reaches into a nearby FVG.",
